10 B. The Advisory Committee shall meet bimonthly to review and
11 make recommendations related to:
12 1. Policy development and program administration;
13 2. Policy changes proposed by the Authority prior to
14 consideration of such changes by the Authority;
15 3. Financial concerns related to the Authority and the
16 administration of the programs under the Authority; and
17 4. Other pertinent information related to the management and
18 operation of the Authority and the delivery of health and medical
19 care services.
20 C. 1. The Administrator of the Authority shall provide such
21 staff support and independent technical assistance as needed by the
22 Advisory Committee to enable the Advisory Committee to make
23 effective recommendations.
